data.name: Planetary Protection
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard a space up to 3 steps away.
data.flavorText: Careful flag contaminated ISRU technology and site a Robonaut there to bring it up to code.

data.name: Planetary Rail Network
data.destination: Colonized Buoyant (M, N or V) colony (no Io)
data.flavorText: Rails can be established and maintained more easily on planets with no atmosphere to corrode them and low gravity.

data.name: Bio-Inspired Rover
data.flavorText: A bio-inspired rover must explore a world of interest to explore life origins instead of explore for minerals.

data.name: Subnubilar Zeppelin
data.flavorText: Arccloud expansions under the Venus or Neptune clouds create an environment for long-term missions.

data.name: Junket
data.flavorText: A publicity only political or promotional site to bring the public or media up to the colony.

data.name: Spaceborn Political Rally
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard a Political card.
data.flavorText: A political rally organized from Earth to free space with tunnel pads and burrows.

data.name: Drug Smuggling
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Discard any 3 cards from hand.
data.flavorText: Illegal drugs, vaccine and life-extension therapies are produced at bioengineering colonies through the use of unique microgravity or exotic environments.

data.name: Chipjack
data.destination: Colonized with a 'Bernal' anywhere and beyond Ceres
data.fulfilledAbility: You may perform instant Operations on a Bernal even if occupied by others.
data.flavorText: Infiltrate and steal secret or proprietary documents and technology files.

data.name: Cancer Research Mission
data.flavorText: Allow humans harvesting an unshielded cycler station or interlude with no other life within a few years and return with samples.

data.name: Trojan Listening Posts
data.flavorText: An observatory placed in orbit around or near a Trojan asteroid could provide years of careful scrutiny of deep space operations while hiding in a swarm.

data.name: Rescue Team
data.flavorText: Investigate loss of life at a now-derelict spacecraft or colony. Discover signs of rebellion.

data.name: Mercury Sunset Convoy
data.destination: Colonized M Colony with Mobility (Operational or Outpost)
data.flavorText: Given Mercury's slow orbit this means a very long journey, one that few others can do.

data.name: SWIV Miner
data.flavorText: Prevent ongoing asteroid or comet mining by claiming their next likely collected and mined target.

data.name: Refueling Trawler
data.flavorText: Provide loiter positions for craft refueling or maintenance to provide deep space presence.

data.name: Tsiolkovsky Elevator Lab
data.fulfilledAbility: Your factory-assist Encrustation cannot be Encrusted at other Elevator as normal burn spaces at Earth Spaces.
data.flavorText: Building a working space elevator would be enormously expensive and this research could lead the way.

data.name: Skyhook
data.destination: Your Factory Site at one end of a Space Elevator icon.
data.requirements: When Fulfilling: Build a Space Elevator at this Site (no Hazard Roll).
data.flavorText: A rotating tether in low orbit can boost payloads via momentum transfer.

data.name: Spin Control
data.flavorText: Working out issues on these contact binary anomalies is excellent research for future asteroid deflections.

data.name: Ring Rain
data.flavorText: The ring of giant planets are resupplied by constant impacts on small shepherd moons and meteoroid bombardment.

data.name: Search for Life Center
data.flavorText: Classify the origin of synthesized life to use, an attempt to achieve, and perhaps replicate abiogenesis.

data.name: Sunrise Project
data.flavorText: The industrial revolution happened alongside fossil fuel revolution. Why can we not similarly do the same with solar magnetic power?

data.name: Yarkovsky Research
data.flavorText: The Yarkovsky effect sets small asteroids spiraling inward or outward, changing projected impact targets by centuries.

data.name: Deep Space One
data.flavorText: Uranus is the easiest source for bulk quantities of He-3, nitrogen, and carbon - all in high demand on Earth.

data.name: Hardened Base
data.flavorText: A heavily-shielded, armor-hardened base typically designed for extended operations in hostile environments.

data.name: Classified Security Payload
data.flavorText: [REDACTED]
